Package data

Class Manga

java.lang.Object
data.Media
data.Manga
public class Manga extends Media
Defines a Manga object as a fundamental part of the log program. Child class of Media. In this program, two Manga cannot have the same name and year.
Author:
Hunter Pruitt

  • Constructor Details

    • Manga

      public Manga(String title, int year, int count, String author, String publishedIn, Media.Type type, boolean finished, boolean dropped, boolean ongoing, String notes)
      Constructor for Manga object, set fields and checks for invalid arguments
      Parameters:
      title - name of entry
      year - release year for first chapter
      count - number chapters read
      author - person(s) who write and draw the story
      publishedIn - source of the Manga
      type - series or special
      finished - if the user finished with the entry
      dropped - if the user stopped watching / reading the entry
      ongoing - if the story has not concluded or is still being serialized
      notes - personal notes about the entry
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if passed bad parameters
